cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to clinical reports, specifically radiology reports. The use of topic modeling to classify these reports is a natural fit for the natural language processing (NLP) subfield of computer science (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of classifiers based on similarity measures, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of aggregate and confidence-based classifiers, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of CT imaging is also mentioned, which could potentially fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) subfield. Finally, the paper deals with the use of electronic health records, which could potentially fall under the cybersecurity (cs.CY) subfield.
